  "prompt": "How does it feel when you read your name in a newspaper for the first time?",
  "response": "Reading your name in a newspaper for the first time can evoke a mix of emotions. Many people feel a sense of pride and validation, especially if the mention is connected to an achievement or recognition. It can also be exciting and surreal, as it signifies that your work or contributions have garnered public attention. There's often a nostalgic element as well, reflecting on the hard work that led to that moment. On the other hand, some might feel nervous or anxious about being in the public eye, depending on the context of the mention. Overall, it\u2019s typically an exhilarating experience!",
